1
00:00:00,218 --> 00:00:02,473
In January 49 B.C.,

2
00:00:02,473 --> 00:00:04,582
Julius Caesar stood at the Rubicon,

3
00:00:04,582 --> 00:00:06,400
the legal edge of Roman Italy.

4
00:00:06,618 --> 00:00:07,782
Crossing it with troops meant

5
00:00:07,782 --> 00:00:09,309
breaking Roman law and turning a

6
00:00:09,309 --> 00:00:11,055
political crisis into rebellion.

7
00:00:11,272 --> 00:00:12,653
Caesar rose through the First

8
00:00:12,653 --> 00:00:14,617
Triumvirate, the consulship, and

9
00:00:14,617 --> 00:00:15,853
conquest in Gaul.

10
00:00:16,072 --> 00:00:17,744
Pompey and his enemies wanted him

11
00:00:17,744 --> 00:00:19,490
back in Rome without command,

12
00:00:19,490 --> 00:00:20,799
exposed to prosecution.

13
00:00:21,017 --> 00:00:22,908
The choice was brutal: return

14
00:00:22,908 --> 00:00:25,017
powerless and fall, or cross armed

15
00:00:25,017 --> 00:00:26,472
and ignite civil war.

16
00:00:26,691 --> 00:00:28,581
Caesar chose the river, carrying his

17
00:00:28,581 --> 00:00:30,036
